Controversy surrounding the construction of a second ferry meant to ease congestion at the Likoni crossing channel has deepened after it emerged that the contractor was demanding additional money. The Turkish firm awarded the tender to build MV Safari wants an additional Sh1 billion the construction of the new vessel had taken long thus market prices of key parts of the vessel had increased. KFS managing director Bakari Gowa said they had began negotiation with the firm to reach at an agreement so that the vessel can be released.